rComments: I liked Prof Okda. She set reasonable expectations, and used a teaching method which was interactive.

I've had the bad luck to have two classes with this prof. She is unclear and boring. I stayed in her class the 2nd time because I wanted a credit I didn't have to do anything for. No textbooks, sometimes attendance is mandatory but not usually and she'll send the slides to you. You won't learn ANYTHING but you will get an easy mark.

I took intro to dev projects, a "technical" course learning how to write project proposals-for this I would take it with her because in the end you learn what you came for & an easy A+. Theory based courses-I'm not so sure I would take with her. Although she was hard to understand she was extremely helpful outside of class & took time to help you.

While she is a bit hard to understand, she isn't completely useless. Her midterm is easy, and she gives marks for attendance. Instead of a final exam, she gives you an assignment, which is min. 7 pages. If you want to boost you CGPA, take a course with her!
Easy course however she is very hard to understand and gives very little directives for assignments and exams. No text book and hardly any readings.
